{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "31", "m": "03", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "04", "M": "25", "S": "47"}}, "news": [{"title": "Fire safety must stay in building code: BIS panel", "para": "A technical committee of the Bureau of Indian Standards (BIS) has opposed the deregulation cell's proposal to remove fire safety provisions from the National Building Code, citing recent fatal fires. While accepting some recommendations, the committee insists fire safety must remain in the code, not as a separate handbook, emphasizing its crucial role in preventing death traps.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/bis-panel-insists-on-fire-safety-in-national-building-code-amid-deregulation-tensions/129914879?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-40404/129914879.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "CAG questions land allotment by Telangana government to Amazon in Pharma City", "para": "The CAG has raised concerns over land allotment for a data centre within the Hyderabad Pharma City. This move deviates from the original plan for a pharmaceutical hub. The audit highlights potential job losses and delays in project implementation. The government maintains the project is on track. Weak monitoring and land management issues were also flagged.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/cag-questions-land-allotment-by-telangana-government-to-amazon-in-pharma-city/129914740?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-1909410/129914740.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "AAI says give clearances for building heights on a case-to-case basis in Mumbai", "para": "A new AAI circular offers hope for stalled Juhu redevelopment projects by establishing a committee to assess building height restrictions near HF transmitters. This move aims to allow case-by-case evaluations, potentially easing current limitations and enabling viable vertical growth while ensuring aviation safety.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/aai-allows-case-by-case-height-clearances-for-redevelopment-projects-in-mumbai/129914637?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-75100/129914637.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}]}